**Workflow:**
User -> Planner;
Planner -> WebSearcher;
WebSearcher -> Summarizer;
Summarizer -> End.

**Description:**
First, the Planner creates a detailed search strategy to locate the oldest closed numpy.polynomial issue with the Regression label on GitHub. Second, the WebSearcher executes this strategy by performing Google searches to find the GitHub repository, navigates through the filtered issues, and extracts the Regression label addition date. Finally, the Summarizer converts the date to MM/DD/YY format and delivers the final answer.
